      "writtenOn": "2016-10-28T13:43:25Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "are you seriously using a single memory region for all guest client connections? This seems really dangerous. There should be a way in this call to identify several independent regions (by id, or something). There should be a way to know when a region is released (what happens if the guest closes the file descriptor but EmuGL is still using the region for some reason, etc...).",
      "revId": "004eb7d898658b3f07cbc83b70dd52613002762f",
